## Problem 2

Show me all of the product descriptions that contain the word "steel" in alphabetical order.

SELECT [Description] 
FROM Production.ProductDescription
WHERE [Description] like '%steel%'
order by [Description]

## Problem 3

How many finished goods products have we offered that require more than 2 days to manufacture?

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM Production.Product
Where FinishedGoodsFlag >=1 and DaysToManufacture >=3

## Problem 4

List all of the work orders that were delivered late.Â  Include the work order's ID, completion date, and due date.

select WorkOrderID, EndDate, DueDate
from Production.WorkOrder
where DueDate < EndDate

## Problem 5

List all of the work orders that were delivered more than 10 days late.Â Â Include the work order's ID, completion date, and due date.

select WorkOrderID, EndDate, DueDate
from Production.WorkOrder
where DATEDIFF(DAY, DueDate,EndDate)>10

## Problem 6 Create a single-column result table with product information for all finished goods in sentence form:â¨â(name) requires (# of days) days to manufacture and has a list price of $(list price)â and sort it by the time required to manufacture with the longest time first.

Select Name + ' requires ' +Cast(DaysToManufacture as varchar) + ' days to manufacture and has a list price of $'+ cast(ListPrice as VARCHAR) 
From Production.Product
WHERE FinishedGoodsFlag=1
ORDER by DaysToManufacture desc
